\par \lquote Pity you can\rquote t attach an extra arm to yours, Malfoy,\rquote  said Harry. Then it could catch the Snitch for you.\rquote 
\par The Gryffindor team laughed loudly. Malfoy\rquote s pale eyes nar\-rowed, and he stalked away. They watched him rejoin the rest of the Slytherin team, who put their heads together, no doubt asking Malfoy whether Harry\rquote s broom really was a Firebolt.

\par At a quarter to eleven, the Gryffindor team set off for the changing rooms. The weather couldn\rquote 
t have been more different from their match against Hufflepuff. It was a clear, cool day, with a very light breeze; there would be no visibility problems this time, and Harry, though nervous, was starting to feel the excitement only a Quidditch 
match could bring. They could hear the rest of the school moving into the stadium beyond. Harry took off his black school robes, removed his wand from his pocket, and stuck it inside the T-shirt he was going to wear under his Quidditch robes. He only hope
d he wouldn\rquote t need it. He wondered suddenly whether Professor Lupin was in the crowd, watching.
\par \lquote You know what we\rquote ve got to do,\rquote  said Wood, as they prepared to leave the changing rooms. \lquote If we lose this match, we\rquote re out of the running. Just \endash  just fly like you did in practice yesterday, and we\rquote 
ll be OK!\rquote 
\par They walked out onto the pitch to tumultuous applause. The Ravenclaw team, dressed in blue, were already standing in the middle of the pitch. Their Seeker, Cho Chang, was the only girl in their team. She was
 shorter than Harry by about a head, and Harry couldn\rquote 
t help noticing, nervous as he was, that she was extremely pretty. She smiled at Harry as the teams faced each other behind their captains, and he felt a slight jolt in the region of his stomach that he didn\rquote t think had anything to do with nerves.

\par \lquote Wood, Davies, shake hands,\rquote  Madam Hooch said briskly, and Wood shook hands with the Ravenclaw captain.
\par \lquote Mount your brooms ... on my whistle ... three \endash  two \endash  one \endash \rquote 
\par Harry kicked off into the air and the Firebolt zoomed higher and faster than any other broom; he soared around the stadium and began squinting around for the Snitch, listening all the while to the commentary, which was being provided by the Weasley twins
\rquote  friend, Lee Jordan.
\par \lquote They\rquote re off, and the big excitement this match is the Firebolt which Harry Potter is flying for Gryffindor. According to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid2125196 Which Broomstick, }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid2125196 the Firebolt\rquote s going to be the broom of choice for the national teams at this year\rquote s World Championship \endash \rquote 
\par \lquote Jordan, would you mind telling us what\rquote s going on in the match?\rquote  interrupted Professor McGonagall\rquote s voice.
\par \lquote Right you are, Professor \endash  just giving a bit of background infor\-mation. The Firebolt, incidentally, has a built-in auto-brake and \endash \rquote 
\par \lquote Jordan!\rquote 
\par \lquote OK, OK, Gryffindor in possession, Katie Bell of Gryffindor heading for goal ...\rquote 
\par Harry streaked past Katie in the opposite direction, gazing around for a glint of gold and noticing that Cho Chang was tailing him closely. She was undoubtedly a very good flier \endash  she kept cut\-ting across him, forcing him to change direction.

\par \lquote Show her your acceleration, Harry!\rquote  Fred yelled, as he whooshed past in pursuit of a Bludger that was aiming for Alicia.
\par Harry urged the Firebolt forward as they rounded the Ravenclaw goalposts and Cho fell behind. Just as Katie succeeded in scoring the first goal of the match, and the Gryffindor end of the pitch went wild, he saw it \endash 
 the Snitch was close to the ground, flitting near one of the barriers.
\par Harry dived; Cho saw what he was doing and tore after him. Harry was speeding up, excitement flooding him; dives were his speciality. He was ten feet away \endash 
\par Then a Bludger, hit by one of the Ravenclaw Beaters, came pelt\-ing out of nowhere; Harry veered off course, avoiding it by an inch, and in those few, crucial seconds, the Snitch had vanished.
\par There was a great \lquote Ooooooh\rquote  of disappointment from the Gryffindor supporters, but much applause for their Beater from the Ravenclaw end. George Weasley vented his feelings by hitting the second Bludger directly at the offending Beat
er, who was forced to roll right over in mid-air to avoid it.
\par \lquote Gryffindor lead by eighty points to zero, and look at that Firebolt go! Potter\rquote s really putting it through its paces now. See it turn \endash  Chang\rquote s Comet is just no match for it. The Firebolt\rquote s pre
cision-balance is really noticeable in these long \endash \rquote 
\par \lquote JORDAN! ARE YOU BEING PAID TO ADVERTISE FIRE\-BOLTS? GET ON WITH THE COMMENTARY!\rquote 
\par Ravenclaw were pulling back; they had now scored three goals, which put Gryffindor only fifty points ahead \endash  if Cho got the Snitch before him, Ravenclaw would win. Harry dropped lower, narrowly avoiding a Ravenclaw Chaser, scanning the pitch franti
\-cally. A glint of gold, a flutter of tiny wings \endash  the Snitch was cir\-cling the Gryffindor goalpost ...
\par Harry accelerated, eyes fixed on the speck of gold ahead \endash  but next second, Cho had appeared out of thin air, blocking him \endash 
\par \lquote HARRY, THIS IS NO TIME TO BE A GENTLEMAN!\rquote  Wood roared, as Harry swerved to avoid a collision. \lquote KNOCK HER OFF HER BROOM IF YOU HAVE TO!\rquote 
\par Harry turned and caught sight of Cho; she was grinning. The Snitch had vanished again. Harry turned his Firebolt upwards and was soon twenty feet above the game. Out of the corner of his eye, he saw Cho following him ... she\rquote 
d decided to mark him rather than search for the Snitch herself. Right then ... if she wanted to tail him, she\rquote d have to take the consequences ...
\par He dived again, and Cho, thinking he\rquote d seen the Snitch, tried to follow. Harry pulled out of the dive very sharply, she hurtled downwards; he ros
e fast as a bullet once more, and then saw it, for the third time: the Snitch was glittering way above the pitch at the Ravenclaw end.
\par He accelerated; so, many feet below, did Cho. He was winning, gaining on the Snitch with every second \endash  then \endash 
\par \lquote Oh!\rquote  screamed Cho, pointing.
\par Distracted, Harry looked down.
\par Three Dementors, three tall, black, hooded Dementors, were looking up at him.
\par He didn\rquote t stop to think. Plunging a hand down the neck of his robes, he whipped out his wand and roared, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid2125196 \lquote Expecto patronum!\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f37\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid2125196 
