 he was nearly there. He stretched out the hand still grasping his wand and just managed to close his fingers over the small, struggling Snitch.
\par Madam Hooch\rquote s whistle sounded, Harry turned around in mid\-air and saw six scarlet blurs bearing down on him. Next moment, the whole team were hugging him so hard he w
as nearly pulled off his broom. Down below he could hear the roars of the Gryffindors in the crowd.
\par \lquote That\rquote s my boy!\rquote  Wood kept yelling. Alicia, Angelina and Katie had all kissed Harry, and Fred had him in a grip so tight Harry felt as though his head would
 come off. In complete disarray, the team managed to make its way back to the ground. Harry got off his broom and looked up to see a gaggle of Gryffindor supporters sprinting onto the pitch, Ron in the lead. Before he knew it, he had been engulfed by the 
cheering crowd.
\par \lquote Yes!\rquote  Ron yelled, yanking Harry\rquote s arm into the air. \lquote Yes! Yes!\rquote 
\par \lquote Well }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid2125196 done, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid2125196 Harry!\rquote  said Percy, looking delighted. \lquote 
Ten Galleons to me! Must find Penelope, excuse me \endash \rquote 
\par \lquote Good on you, Harry!\rquote  roared Seamus Finnigan.
\par \lquote Ruddy brilliant!\rquote  boomed Hagrid over the heads of the milling Gryffindors.
\par \lquote That was quite some Patronus,\rquote  said a voice in Harry\rquote s ear.
\par Harry turned around to see Professor Lupin, who looked both shaken and pleased.
\par \lquote The Dementors didn\rquote t affect me at all!\rquote  Harry said excitedly. \lquote I didn\rquote t feel a thing!\rquote 
\par \lquote That would be because they \endash  er \endash  weren\rquote t Dementors,\rquote  said Professor Lupin. \lquote Come and see \endash \rquote 
\par He led Harry out of the crowd until they were able to see the edge of the pitch.
\par \lquote You gave Mr Malfoy quite a fright,\rquote  said Lupin.
\par Harry stared. Lying in a crumpled heap on the ground were Malfoy, Crabbe, Goyle and Marcus Flint, the Slytherin team cap\-tain, all struggling to remove themselves from long, black, hooded robes. It looked as though Malfoy had been standing on Goyle
\rquote s shoulders. Standing over them, with an expression of the utmost fury on her face, was Professor McGonagall.
\par \lquote An unworthy trick!\rquote  she was shouting. \lquote A low and cowardly attempt to sabotage the Gryffindor Seeker! Detention for all of you, and fifty points from Slytherin! 
I shall be speaking to Professor Dumbledore about this, make no mistake! Ah, here he comes now!\rquote 
\par If anything could have set the seal on Gryffindor\rquote s victory, it was this. Ron, who had fought his way through to Harry\rquote s side, doubled up with laughter as they watched Malfoy fighting to extricate himself from the robe, Goyle\rquote 
s head still stuck inside it.
\par \lquote Come on, Harry!\rquote  said George, fighting his way over. \lquote Party! Gryffindor common room, now!\rquote 
\par \lquote Right,\rquote  said Harry, and feeling happier than he had done in ages, he and the rest of the team led the way, still in their scarlet robes, out of the stadium and back up to the castle.
