\par \lquote All unconscious by the time I reached them. I bound and gagged Black, naturally, conjured stretchers and brought them all straight back to the castle.\rquote 
\par There was a pause. Harry\rquote s brain seemed to be moving a little faster, and as it did, a gnawing sensation grew in the pit of his stomach ...
\par He opened his eyes.
\par Everything was slightly blurred. Somebody had removed his glasses. He was lying in the dark hospital wing. At the very end of the ward, he could make out Madam Pomfrey with her back to him, bending over a bed. Harry squinted. Ron\rquote 
s red hair was visi\-ble beneath Madam Pomfrey\rquote s arm.
\par Harry moved his head over on the pillow. In the bed to his right lay Hermione. Moonlight was falling across her bed. Her eyes were open, too. She looked petrified, and when she saw that Harry was awake, pressed a finger to her li
ps, then pointed to the hospital-wing door. It was ajar, and the voices of Cornelius Fudge and Snape were coming through it from the corridor outside.
\par Madam Pomfrey now came walking briskly up the dark ward to Harry\rquote s bed. He turned to look at her. She was carrying the largest block of chocolate he had ever seen in his life. It looked like a small boulder.
\par \lquote Ah, you\rquote re awake!\rquote  she said briskly. She placed the chocolate on Harry\rquote s bedside table and began breaking it apart with a small hammer.
\par \lquote How\rquote s Ron?\rquote  said Harry and Hermione together.
\par \lquote He\rquote ll live,\rquote  said Madam Pomfrey grimly. \lquote As for you two ... you\rquote ll be staying here until I\rquote m satisfied you\rquote re \endash  Potter, what do you think you\rquote re doing?\rquote 
\par Harry was sitting up, putting his glasses back on and picking up his wand.
\par \lquote I need to see the Headmaster,\rquote  he said.
\par \lquote Potter,\rquote  said Madam Pomfrey soothingly, \lquote it\rquote s all right. They\rquote ve got Black. He\rquote s locked away upstairs. The Dementors will be per\-forming the Kiss any moment now \endash \rquote 
\par \lquote WHAT?\rquote 
\par Harry jumped up out of bed; Hermione had done the same. But his shout had been heard in the corridor outside; next second, Cornelius Fudge and Snape had entered the ward.
\par \lquote Harry, Harry, what\rquote s this?\rquote  said Fudge, looking agitated. \lquote You should be in bed \endash  has he had any chocolate?\rquote  he asked Madam Pomfrey anxiously.
\par \lquote Minister, listen!\rquote  Harry said. \lquote Sirius Black\rquote s innocent! Peter Pettigrew faked his own death! We saw him tonight! You can\rquote t let the Dementors do that thing to Sirius, he\rquote s \endash \rquote 
\par But Fudge was shaking his head with a small smile on his face.
\par \lquote Harry, Harry, you\rquote re very confused, you\rquote ve been through a dreadful ordeal, lie back down, now, we\rquote ve got everything under control ...\rquote 
\par \lquote YOU HAVEN\rquote T!\rquote  Harry yelled. \lquote YOU\rquote VE GOT THE WRONG MAN!\rquote 
\par \lquote Minister, listen, please,\rquote  Hermione said; she had hurried to Harry\rquote s side and was gazing imploringly into Fudge\rquote s face. \lquote I saw him, too. It was Ron\rquote s rat, he\rquote s an Animagus, Pettigrew, I mean, and \endash 
\rquote 
\par \lquote You see, Minister?\rquote  said Snape. \lquote Confunded, both of them ... Black\rquote s done a very good job on them ...\rquote 
\par \lquote WE\rquote RE NOT CONFUNDED!\rquote  Harry roared.
\par \lquote Minister! Professor!\rquote  said Madam Pomfrey angrily. \lquote I must insist that you leave. Potter is my patient, and he should not be distressed!\rquote 
\par \lquote I\rquote m not distressed, I\rquote m trying to tell them what happened!\rquote  Harry said furiously. \lquote If they\rquote d just listen \endash \rquote 
\par But Madam Pomfrey suddenly stuffed a large chunk of choco\-late into Harry\rquote s mouth. He choked, and she seized the opportun\-ity to force him back onto the bed.
\par \lquote Now, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid2125196 please, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid2125196 Minister, these children need care. Please leave \endash 
\rquote 
