\par \lquote That, indeed, is Black\rquote s story,\rquote  said Dumbledore, surveying Snape closely through his half-moon spectacles.
\par \lquote And does my evidence count for nothing?\rquote  snarled Snape. \lquote Peter Pettigrew was not in the Shrieking Shack, nor did I see any sign of him in the grounds.\rquote 
\par \lquote That was because you were knocked out, Professor!\rquote  said Hermione earnestly. \lquote You didn\rquote t arrive in time to hear \endash \rquote 
\par \lquote Miss Granger, HOLD YOUR TONGUE!\rquote 
\par \lquote Now, Snape,\rquote  said Fudge, startled, \lquote the young lady is disturbed in her mind, we must make allowances \endash \rquote 
\par \lquote I would like to speak to Harry and Hermione alone,\rquote  said Dumbledore abruptly. \lquote Cornelius, Severus, Poppy \endash  please leave us.\rquote 
\par \lquote Headmaster!\rquote  spluttered Madam Pomfrey. \lquote They need treat\-ment, they need rest \endash \rquote 
\par \lquote This cannot wait,\rquote  said Dumbledore. \lquote I must insist.\rquote 
