\par \lquote Professor Lupin is currently deep in the Forest, unable to tell anyone anything. By the time he is human again, it will be too late, Sirius will
 be worse than dead. I might add that werewolves are so mistrusted by most of our kind that his support will count for very little \endash  and the fact that he and Sirius are old friends \endash \rquote 
\par \lquote But \endash \rquote 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid2125196 \lquote Listen to me, Harry. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid2125196 
It is too late, you understand me? You must see that Professor Snape\rquote s version of events is far more convincing than yours.\rquote 
\par \lquote He hates Sirius,\rquote  Hermione said desperately. \lquote All because of some stupid trick Sirius played on him \endash \rquote 
\par \lquote Sirius has not acted like an innocent man. The attack on the Fat Lady \endash  entering Gryffindor Tower with a knife \endash  without Pettigrew, alive or dead, we have no chance of overturning Sirius\rquote  sentence.\rquote 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid2125196 \lquote But you believe us.\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid2125196 
\par \lquote Yes, I do,\rquote  said Dumbledore quietly. \lquote But I have no power to make other men see the truth, or to overrule the Minister for Magic ...\rquote 
\par Harry stared up into the grave face and felt as though the ground beneath him was falling sharply away. He had grown used to the idea that Dumbledore could solve anything. He had expect\-
ed Dumbledore to pull some amazing solution out of the air. But no ... their last hope was gone.
\par \lquote What we need,\rquote  said Dumbledore slowly, and his light-blue eyes moved from Harry to Hermione, \lquote is more }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f37\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid2125196 time.\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 
