\par \lquote Here \endash \rquote 
\par She had thrown the chain around his neck, too.
\par \lquote Ready?\rquote  she said breathlessly.
\par \lquote What are we doing?\rquote  Harry said, completely lost.
\par Hermione turned the hour-glass over three times.
\par The dark ward dissolved. Harry had the sensation that he was flying, very fast, backwards. A blur of colours and shapes rushed past him; his ears were pounding. He tried to yell but couldn\rquote t hear his own voice \endash 
\par And then he felt solid ground beneath his feet, and everything came into focus again \endash 
\par He was standing next to Hermione in the deserted Entrance Hall and a stream of golden sunlight was falling across the paved floor from the open front doors. He looked wildly around at Hermione, the chain of the hour-glass cutting into his neck.
\par \lquote Hermione, what \endash ?\rquote 
\par \lquote In here!\rquote  Hermione seized Harry\rquote s arm and dragged him across the hall to the door of a broom cupboard; she opened it, pushed him inside amongst the buckets and mops, followed him in, then slammed the door behind them.
\par \lquote What \endash  how \endash  Hermione, what happened?\rquote 
\par \lquote We\rquote ve gone back in time,\rquote  Hermione whispered, lifting the chain off Harry\rquote s neck in the darkness. \lquote Three hours back ...\rquote 
\par Harry found his own leg and gave it a very hard pinch. It hurt a lot, which seemed to rule out the possibility that he was having a very bizarre dream.
\par \lquote But \endash \rquote 
\par \lquote Shh! Listen! Someone\rquote s coming! I think \endash  I think it might be us!\rquote 
\par Hermione had her ear pressed against the cupboard door.
\par \lquote Footsteps across the hall ... yes, I think it\rquote s us going down to Hagrid\rquote s!\rquote 
\par \lquote Are you telling me,\rquote  Harry whispered, \lquote that we\rquote re here in this cupboard and we\rquote re out there, too?\rquote 
\par \lquote Yes,\rquote  said Hermione, her ear still glued to the cupboard door. \lquote I\rquote m sure it\rquote s us ... it doesn\rquote t sound like more than three people ... and we\rquote re walking slowly because we\rquote 
re under the Invisibility Cloak \endash \rquote 
\par She broke off, still listening intently.
\par \lquote We\rquote ve gone down the front steps ...\rquote 
