In here!\rquote 
\par They tore into a deserted classroom to their left just in time. Peeves seemed to be bouncing along the corridor in tearing spir\-its, laughing his head off.
\par \lquote Oh, he\rquote s horrible,\rquote  whispered Hermione, her ear to the door. \lquote I bet he\rquote s all excited because the Dementors are going to finish Sirius ...\rquote  She checked her watch. \lquote Three minutes, Harry!\rquote 
\par They waited until Peeves\rquote s gloating voice had faded into the dis\-tance, then slid back out of the room and broke into a run again.
\par \lquote Hermione \endash  what\rquote ll happen \endash  if we don\rquote t get back inside \endash  before Dumbledore locks the door?\rquote  Harry panted.
\par \lquote I don\rquote t want to think about it!\rquote  Hermione moaned, checking her watch again. \lquote One minute!\rquote 
\par They had reached the end of the corridor with the hospital-wing entrance. \lquote OK \endash  I can hear Dumbledore,\rquote  said Hermione tensely. \lquote Come on, Harry!\rquote 
\par They crept along the corridor. The door opened. Dumbledore\rquote s back appeared.
\par \lquote I am going to lock you in,\rquote  they heard him saying. \lquote It is five minutes to midnight. Miss Granger, three turns should do it. Good luck.\rquote 
\par Dumbledore backed out of the room, closed the door and took out his wand to magically lock it. Panicking, Harry and Hermione ran forwards. Dumbledore looked up, and a wide smile appeared under the long silver moustache. \lquote Well?\rquote 
 he said quietly.
\par \lquote We did it!\rquote  said Harry breathlessly. \lquote Sirius has gone, on Buckbeak ...\rquote 
\par Dumbledore beamed at them.
\par \lquote Well done. I think \endash \rquote  he listened intently for any sound within the hospital wing. \lquote Yes, I think you\rquote ve gone, too. Get inside \endash  I\rquote ll lock you in \endash \rquote 
\par Harry and Hermione slipped back inside the dormitory. It was empty except for Ron, who was still lying motionless in the end bed. As the lock clicked behind them, Harry and Hermione crept back to their own bed
s, Hermione tucking the Time-Turner back under her robes. Next moment, Madam Pomfrey had come strid\-ing back out of her office.
\par \lquote Did I hear the Headmaster leaving? Am I allowed to look after my patients now?\rquote 
\par She was in a very bad mood. Harry and Hermione thought it best to accept their chocolate quietly. Madam Pomfrey stood over them, making sure they ate it. But Harry could hardly swallow. He and Hermione were waiting, listening, their nerves jangling ... An
d then, as they both took a fourth piece of chocolate from Madam Pomfrey, they heard a distant roar of fury echoing from somewhere above them ...
\par \lquote What was that?\rquote  said Madam Pomfrey in alarm.
\par Now they could hear angry voices, growing louder and louder. Madam Pomfrey was staring at the door.
\par \lquote Really \endash  they\rquote ll wake everybody up! What do they think they\rquote re doing?\rquote 
\par Harry was trying to hear what the voices were saying. They were drawing nearer \endash 
\par \lquote He must have Disapparated, Severus, we should have left somebody in the room with him. When this gets out \endash \rquote 
\par \lquote HE DIDN\rquote T DISAPPARATE!\rquote  Snape roared, now very close at hand. \lquote YOU CAN\rquote T APPARATE OR DISAPPARATE INSIDE THIS CASTLE! THIS \endash  HAS \endash  SOMETHING \endash  TO \endash  DO \endash  WITH \endash  POTTER!\rquote 

\par \lquote Severus \endash  be reasonable \endash  Harry has been locked up \endash \rquote 
\par BAM.
\par The door of the hospital wing burst open.
\par Fudge, Snape and Dumbledore came striding into the ward. Dumbledore alone looked calm. Indeed, he looked as though he was quite enjoying himself. Fudge appeared angry. But Snape was beside himself.
\par \lquote OUT WITH IT, POTTER!\rquote  he bellowed. \lquote WHAT DID YOU DO?\rquote 
\par \lquote Professor Snape!\rquote  shrieked Madam Pomfrey. \lquote Control yourself!\rquote 
\par \lquote See here, Snape, be reasonable,\rquote  said Fudge. \lquote This door\rquote s been locked, we just saw \endash \rquote 
\par \lquote THEY HELPED HIM ESCAPE, I KNOW IT!\rquote  Snape howled, pointing at Harry and Hermione. His face was twisted, spit was flying from his mouth.
\par \lquote Calm down, man!\rquote  Fudge barked. \lquote You\rquote re talking nonsense!\rquote 
\par \lquote YOU DON\rquote T KNOW POTTER!\rquote  shrieked Snape. \lquote HE DID IT, I KNOW HE DID IT \endash \rquote 
\par \lquote That will do, Severus,\rquote  said Dumbledore quietly. \lquote Think about what you are saying. This door has been locked since I left the ward ten minutes ago. Madam Pomfrey, have these students left their beds?\rquote 
\par \lquote Of course not!\rquote  said Madam Pomfrey, bristling. \lquote I\rquote ve been with them ever since you left!\rquote 
\par \lquote Well, there you have it, Severus,\rquote  said Dumbledore calmly. \lquote Unless you are suggesting that Harry and Hermione are able to be in two places at once, I\rquote m afraid I don\rquote t see any point in troubling them further.\rquote 

\par Snape stood there, seething, staring from Fudge, who looked thoroughly shocked at his behaviour, to Dumbledore, whose eyes were twinkling behind his glasses. Snape whirled about, robes swishing behind him, and stormed out of the ward.
\par \lquote Fellow seems quite unbalanced,\rquote  said Fudge, staring after him. \lquote I\rquote d watch out for him, if I were you, Dumbledore.\rquote 
